Hmm but there's very little new about WoW? WTF are you smoking? WoW is going to be the game that EQ should have been. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mitebe1>MiteBe1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 716<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/03 9:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQII vs WoW Graphics</span><hr size=1> The real reason I hold out hope for WoW over other games and EQ2 in particular is the history of the company. Blizzard has a history of delaying the game to get it right the first time and releasing quality enjoyable software. Verant/SOE had (has?) a history of releasing software in a late beta state and attempting to patch on the fly. The improved quality of PoP is, to me, more an indication SOE's awareness of impending competition in the marketplace moreso then a genuine love of the game. They figured that to retain customers and extend the brand's good name they would need to improve customer relations by improving game play/quality.<br>
<br>
Now of course this is a new type of game for Blizzard but as long as they adhere to their basic tenets that got them this far I see no reason to expect anything other than a good game. The biggest challenge for Blizzard is coming up with enough content to keep people interesting in the game beyond the first few months. I have read that this is in fact why they are not releasing the game at this point as the gameplay movies seem to show a pretty sound engine. <br>
<br>
Time will tell who will win the next round but suffice to say that this next year will see SOE's first legitimate competition from more than one company and many of them with as deep if not deeper pockets than Sony. It may very well be that everyone will win because it may just be that the marketplace is big enough to have more than one company survives in this genre.<br>
<br>
I like the graphics from both games. I like the realistic look of EQ2 and I like the cartoony character of WoW. The real proof of the pudding will be content, gameplay, quality (read lack of bugs) and customer support. Blizzard has always had the first 3 nailed but this will be their first real baptism of fire in an MMORPG type game. SOE has decent content, has steadily improved gameplay and has questionable quality and CS, and EQ2 has different gameplay due to the reworked character development.<br>
<br>
I think one thing that everyone can agree on is whether you are rooting for and ultimately choose WoW, EQ2 or BrandX, we (the customer) are the ultimate winners of this increased competition. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artillis>Artillis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Enjoys Sheep Erotica</span><br>  Posts: 1842<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/03 9:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQII vs WoW Graphics</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I think one thing that everyone can agree on is whether you are rooting for and ultimately choose WoW, EQ2 or BrandX, we (the customer) are the ultimate winners of this increased competition. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
