<br>
So... I like the realism of EQ2.  But I rather like the artful look of WoW.  It adds character and style to the game.  Which EQ2's graphics lack for me.  They both have great graphics stylistically and it is the difference in them that make each stand out.  I will say that I prefer the artistic look of WoW to EQ2.  However, I want to see more of the spell effects.  The few I have seen have been unappealing when compared to EQ2.<br>
<br>
As to which game will be better and who has the better experience with what.  Well, that will all be seen later.  Yes, Blizzard has an amazing track record for nearly every topic that can be mentioned.  But they have zero experience with MMOG's.  VI/SoE has 4 years.  Blizzards CS has always been very good, even excellent.  However, they have never dealt with an MMOG before.  It is reasonable to assume that they will continue to do so and I have faith in that.  Still, this is new for them.  They are not impervious to making errors.  It also bares mentioning that since SoE purchased VI, things... they are a-changin'.  EQ has become a better game as a result.  I have personally never had any issues with GM's.  They have always been polite, reasonable, and prompt.  I did have an unsavory experience with phone tech support.  As it turned out though, it was a problem with my machine and not their code.<br>
<br>
Preferences is what this all boils down to.  Do you prefer the World of Warcraft or Everquest II.  These games are not out yet.  Wait until they are to decide.  It sure is fun to talk about them though!!  =D<br>
